<TITLE> US says `extremely concerned' about Pakistan security </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINGTON, Fri Apr 24, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The United States is `extremely concerned' about the security situation in Pakistan, the White House said on Thursday, a day after Washington said Islamabad had abdicated to militants in the Swat valley region. Taliban militants have pushed closer to the capital Islamabad in recent days, saying their aim was to impose their harsh version of Islam across Pakistan. Unidentified gunmen attacked paramilitary troops who deployed to a district in the region on Thursday, killing a policeman escorting them. "I think the news over the past several days is very disturbing. We're extremely concerned about the situation and it's something that takes a lot of the president's time," White House spokesman Robert Gibbs told a news confer
